"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.1.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.1.4</span> Muzzle</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חסם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(chasam (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:4\">DEU 25:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מַחְסוֹם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(machsom)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:2\">PSA 39:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">φιμός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(fimos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir20:29\">SIR 20:29</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">φιμόω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(fimoō (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sus1:60\">SUS 1:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc1:35\">4MA 1:35</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κημόω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kēmoō (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:9\">1CO 9:9</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0318_muzzle.jpg\" alt=\"Muzzled cow used for threshing\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Muzzled cow used for threshing (Matson Collection, Library of Congress, Public domain)</figcaption></figure>The muzzle was a guard placed over or around the mouth of an animal to prevent it from biting or eating. It was made of rope or leather strips formed into a loose mesh; this allowed the animal to breathe while preventing it from getting anything into its mouth.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The two New Testament references are quotations from <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:4\">DEU 25:4</a> (where <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:18</a> follows the Septuagint and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:9\">1CO 9:9</a> uses an equivalent verb). In some languages it may be necessary to use some kind of descriptive equivalent of “to muzzle an ox,” for example, “to tie the mouth of an ox so that it cannot eat” or “to cover the mouth of an ox so that it cannot eat.” In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:2\">PSA 39:2</a> the literal text “I will guard my mouth with a muzzle” may be rendered “I will keep silent” (compare <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> “I will not say anything”).</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
